12
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:34,360
and therefore the class name should reflect

13
00:00:34,360 --> 00:00:36,840
which kind of object gets created.

14
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:39,710
Hence, classes might be named something like user

15
00:00:39,710 --> 00:00:43,210
or product if they reflect these objects.

16
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:46,090
You can, as always, provide more details if it makes sense

17
00:00:46,090 --> 00:00:48,000
and doesn't add redundancy.

18
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,360
So your user class could become a customer class,

19
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:54,370
your product class could become a course class

20
00:00:54,370 --> 00:00:56,990
if your product is an online course.

21
00:00:56,990 --> 00:01:00,680
You can also use more than one word for class names,

22
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:03,100
but you should avoid redundant suffixes,

23
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:05,200
like DatabaseManager.

24
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:08,570
It can be intriguing to sometimes use names like this,

25
00:01:08,570 --> 00:01:12,340
